Combine the chocolate chips, milk, corn, and salt in a small saucepan over low heat. Stir and cook until chocolate is melted. Remove from heat and stir in the vanilla. Line a square dish with waxed paper. Spread the chocolate mixture into the lined dish. Chill in refrigerator until firm, about 2 hours. Peel off waxed paper and cut into small squares. Store covered in refrigerator.